<td><FONT SIZE="1" FACE="Verdana, Arial" COLOR="#2f2f4f">Originally posted by Perplex on 05-29-2002 04:37 PM<BR></FONT>
<TEXTAREA NAME="EditedMessage" ROWS=10 COLS=45 WRAP="VIRTUAL">There's a simple solution.

Make more encounters that don't involve a single mob that quads ungodly amount of damage per hit, and that don't involve a single tank holding aggro with a chain of clerics to compensate for the damage output.

Any encounter where half the people can go afk after they turn on auto-attack is a good example of how things shouldn't be done. AoW is basic example. Fun encounter for a cleric, but other than MT, who else does anything other than try not to take aggro and push a disc button?

Instead, make more encounters that last 30 minutes or more with reasonable damage rate and deal with multiple mobs at the same time, behaving in certain pre defined pattern with some degree of randomness. So that the encounter involves orchestrating pretty much every single person involved in real-time and requires skill on everyone's behalf, instead of relying 100% on clerics to do most of the work.

Any encounter where you sat at the edge of your seat the whole time and actually gave some *thought* about what you need to do to help the situation, is how it should be done.

Good example of a fun encounter that isn't totally dependent on clerics, imho is Shei Vinitras.

Make encounters be like an evening movie... Something that lasts longer than 5-10 minutes max which leaves you hungry for more action. Why not try to come up with encounter that provides you with an hour or two of entertainment, with few minute breaks every 20 minutes which would give you time to go to bathroom (simmilar to Burrower waves).

Endurance fights are where people are pushed to their limits, instead of 5 minute fight that is all about your DPS and the number of clerics that you can string.

Now before you say Ring of Fire.. forget it. Ring of Fire is dull and unimaginative. Same thing happens over and over with same exact mobs for infinite amount of time. What I'm talking about is more involved than that. Perhaps make it a multi part event like Coldain war, where you have to fight several mini bosses to get to the head honcho, and each of those mini bosses has his own environment and behaviour pattern.

Make the encounter keep a raiding guild occupied for the whole evening, make it fun, and give good rewards, instead of having twenty 5 minute mobs that bunch of guilds compete for, and once they are all killed, there's nothing left to do.

IMHO, the issue really isn't that the game is too dependent on Clerics - that is a side effect. The real issue is that the end game is horribly messed up. There is a serious lack of content for the number of people who are looking for it.



[This message has been edited by Perplex (edited 05-29-2002).]</TEXTAREA>
</td></tr>
